cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.DB 

The paper presents a system for online probabilistic event forecasting using a probabilistic model based on Pattern Markov Chains. This involves machine learning techniques and data analysis, which are typically associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The system also involves real-time processing and updating of forecasts, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the system deals with streams of events and probabilistic modeling, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases).
